Three nurses and a cleaner have been charged with the murder of a cancer patient. Priscilla Wairimu, Godfrey Muriithi Gachora, Rosemary Nkonge and Mary Muthoni Kamau, who were arraigned before High Court Judge Jessi Lesiit today, have denied killing Cosmas Mutunga Kenyatta. Mr Kenyatta was allegedly killed on the night of November 28 and 29, 2015 in ward 8C of Kenyatta National Hospital. The accused will be detained at the Lang'ata and Industrial Area prisons as they await a bail hearing, with their trial set for March 6 and 9, 2017.  